        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 1:14AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 114 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Broadus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Broadus.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
